<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6644] Support standard syntax for altering column nullability</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6644</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Derby supports altering the nullability of a column via an ALTER TABLE statement, but the supported syntax is different from what the SQL:2011 standard defines. We should add support for the standard syntax as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The standard syntax is&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  ALTER TABLE t ALTER COLUMN c SET NOT NULL&lt;br/&gt;
  ALTER TABLE t ALTER COLUMN c DROP NOT NULL&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
